@node carg
@section @code{carg}, @code{cargf}---argument (phase angle)
@findex carg
@findex cargf
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <complex.h>
double carg(double complex @var{z});
float cargf(float complex @var{z});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
These functions compute the argument (also called phase angle) 
of @var{z}, with a branch cut along the negative real axis.

@code{cargf} is identical to @code{carg}, except that it performs
its calculations on @code{floats complex}.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
@ifnottex
The carg functions return the value of the argument in the 
interval [-pi, +pi]
@end ifnottex
@tex
The carg functions return the value of the argument in the 
interval [$-\pi$, $+\pi$]
@end tex

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{carg} and @code{cargf} are ISO C99

@*
